('2008-04-30', '11:04:00', 4645, 'Jackdaw (Corvus monedula)', '6 birds in total. Feeding on the bird feeder put in the apple tree in such a position that I thought only small birds could get to it. The Jackdaw&#39;s solution was ingenious. They moved around the SE corner of the site as a loose group, feeding on the ground and compost heaps and collecting some nesting material hung up in a nearby apple tree.', 'Alive', '2', -1.612415314, 54.99029558, 'gardener'),
