('2008-04-30', '11:04:00', 4465, 'House Sparrow (Passer domesticus)', 'Group of house sparrows are regular, daily visitors to the backyard. Feed on both the birdfeeders and have stripped large areas of a small pussy willow tree of buds. Also take lots of nesting material - combings from a Golden Retriever being the favourite. Maximum number seen at any one time - 5 females and 4 males. They nest in the dense, tall bushes in the backyards of the 2 houses immediately to the east.', 'Alive', '2', -1.601890326, 54.98897217, 'gardener'),
