('2009-05-31', '06:05:00', 2234, 'Cow Parsley (Anthriscus sylvestris)', 'There were masses of cow parsley growing in the verges until today when the farmer came along and mowed them down. Our road is not a &quot;strategic road&quot; so why did he do this? As I understand the situation non- strategic roads should be cut once a year in July. Last year the verges near our house were cut 4 times! As a result of all this mowing native flowers are disappearing which has a knock on effect. No flowers means fewer bees butterflies and insects and of course that effects the feeding of young birds at this time of year.I am furious about this destruction of habitat which is so important to maintain wildlife.', 'Alive', '2', -2.043800354, 55.66047284, 'Ruby'),
('2009-05-31', '06:05:00', 5584, 'Meadow Buttercup (Ranunculus acris)', 'There were masses growing along the verges until today when a farmer came along and mowed them down, along with all the other flowers previously recorded by me!See my previous note on cow parsley. How can we possibly help wildlife when this happens regularly?', 'Alive', '2', -2.043671608, 55.66054546, 'Ruby'),
('2009-05-31', '06:05:00', 9976, 'Wood Avens (Geum urbanum)', 'Lots of plants growing in the verges until today when a farmer came along and mowed them down!See my note on cow parsley. This constant mowing in an area where flowers grow like a meadow has resulted in the loss of such plants as Quaking grass, yellow rattle and field scabious. Really, this is a situation which ought to be addressed given that people are being asked to encourage wildlife and preserve it.', 'Alive', '2', -2.043886185, 55.66049705, 'Ruby'),
