('2009-06-13', '03:06:00', 3814, 'Great Spotted Woodpecker (Dendrocopos major)', '2, male gorging on peanuts, which it does all day long, occasionally flying onto trunk of cherry tree where he taps at the grooves in the trunk either cleaning beak or trying to store bits of peanut.He is very aggressive towards the female and will chase her away with a great deal of noise, even when she is feeding at another feeder. He even flew at her and knocked her off the feeder. In other words he is being a pain. Occasionally he flies off in the direction of Harbour Wood when the female seizes her opportunity and feeds in peace but he soon reappears and chases her away. This male bird is so used to seeing me that it sits in the tree squawking at me as I fill the feeders! Bossy cteature!1 male, 1 female.', 'Alive', '2', -2.043886185, 55.66122329, 'Ruby'),
